+-Here is the Phase 7.3 — Scene Execution Layer file-by-file implementation spec for the coding LLM.
+-
+-This phase turns your current control layer into a full gameplay loop:
+-
+-ChoiceSet / ChoiceOption exist
+-GM and pacing/framing can shape options
+-now player choice must resolve into structured events
+-those events must flow through EventBus
+-CoherenceCore must absorb them
+-director/renderer then consume updated truth
+-
+-The key rule for 7.3:
+-
+-Option selection never mutates state directly.
+-It resolves into events, and existing reducers/system boundaries remain the authority path.
+-
+-This preserves:
+-
+-determinism
+-replay/snapshot safety
+-coherence authority
+-inspectability/debugging
+-Phase 7.3 goals
+-Main outcomes
+-Structured action resolution
+-selecting an option results in an explicit ResolvedAction
+-that action emits deterministic events
+-Option types gain gameplay meaning
+-investigate_thread
+-talk_to_npc
+-travel_to_location
+-press_for_reveal
+-reduce_tension
+-request_recap
+-Consequences become explicit
+-not just prose
+-not direct state mutation
+-emitted as structured events
+-Scene transitions become formalized
+-especially location travel and focus changes
+-Action traces become inspectable
+-“why did this action emit these events?”
+-useful for debugging and GM tools later
+-New package
+-
+-Create:
+-
+-src/app/rpg/execution/__init__.py
+-src/app/rpg/execution/models.py
+-src/app/rpg/execution/intent_mapping.py
+-src/app/rpg/execution/consequences.py
+-src/app/rpg/execution/transitions.py
+-src/app/rpg/execution/resolver.py
+-
+-Keep execution separate from:
+-
+-creator setup
+-narrative renderer
+-coherence core
